---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About CheckIfLegit"
  description="How CheckIfLegit assesses online stores using public trust signals."
>
  <h1>About CheckIfLegit</h1>
  <p>
    CheckIfLegit publishes automated, plain-language summaries of the public trust
    signals around online stores. For each store we check, where possible:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>How long the domain has been registered (via public WHOIS records)</li>
    <li>Whether the site has a valid SSL/HTTPS certificate</li>
    <li>Whether the homepage loads and links to standard contact and policy pages</li>
    <li>Whether public business contact details are listed</li>
    <li>Whether the store has a third-party review presence (e.g. Trustpilot)</li>
    <li>Whether it links to established social media profiles</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>What this is — and isn't</h2>
  <p>
    Every assessment is generated from information that is publicly available at the time
    of checking. A signal we cannot verify is reported as <em>unknown</em> — we never guess.
    These summaries are <strong>not</strong> a definitive judgement of any business, and we
    do not label businesses as scams. They are a starting point for your own research.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you operate a store we have checked and believe something is inaccurate or out of date,
    email <a href="mailto:hello@checkiflegit.com">hello@checkiflegit.com</a> and we will review it.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
